      "id": "jewish_bride",
      "name": "The Jewish Bride",
      "pid": "8",
      "text": "# The Jewish Bride\n## Rembrandt van Rijn, c. 1665-1669\n\n![The Jewish Bride](assets/images/jewish_bride.jpg)\n\n**Location:** Floor 2, Room 2.8  \n**QR Code:** RIJKS-BRIDE-005\n\n[audio](assets/audio/en/jewish_bride.mp3)\n\n### A Masterpiece of Love\n\nVincent van Gogh said he would give ten years of his life to sit before this painting for two weeks with only a crust of bread to eat. That's how powerful *The Jewish Bride* is.\n\n### The Mystery\n\n**Who are they?**\nDespite the traditional title, we don't know if the couple is Jewish, or even if it's a bride. Theories:\n- Biblical Isaac and Rebekah\n- A wealthy Amsterdam couple in costume\n- Rembrandt's son Titus and his bride\n\nWhat we do know: This is one of art's greatest depictions of love, tenderness, and intimacy.\n\n### The Touch\n\nLook at their hands:\n- His right hand gently on her heart\n- Her hand tenderly covering his\n- The intimacy is palpable\n\nThis gesture‚Äîso simple, so human‚Äîhas moved viewers for 350 years.\n\n### Rembrandt's Late Style\n\nBy this period, Rembrandt painted with unprecedented freedom. The clothing is built up with thick, almost sculptural paint. The faces glow with inner light. Colors are rich, warm, golden.\n\nRembrandt has transcended technique‚Äîthis is pure emotion made visible.\n\n---\n\n**Moving to Floor 1:** Still Life and Seascapes",
