      "text": "# The Threatened Swan\n## Jan Asselijn, c. 1650\n\n![The Threatened Swan](assets/images/threatened_swan.jpg)\n\n**Location:** Floor 1, Room 1.6  \n**QR Code:** RIJKS-SWAN-007\n\n[audio](assets/audio/en/threatened_swan.mp3)\n\n### Political Allegory\n\nThis isn't just a swan‚Äîit's the Netherlands itself! The swan represents the Dutch statesman Johan de Witt defending the country (the eggs) against enemies (the dog).\n\nNotice the swan's aggressive posture, spread wings, and protective stance over the nest. This painting was political propaganda disguised as a nature scene.\n\n---\n\n**Next:** Winter Landscape",
