      "text": "# Winter Landscape with Ice Skaters\n## Hendrick Avercamp, c. 1608\n\n![Winter Landscape](assets/images/winter_landscape.jpg)\n\n**Location:** Floor 1, Room 1.13  \n**QR Code:** RIJKS-WINTER-008\n\n[audio](assets/audio/en/winter_landscape.mp3)\n\n### A Frozen World\n\nAvercamp specialized in winter scenes, capturing Dutch life during the Little Ice Age when winters were much colder than today. The frozen canals became highways and gathering places.\n\n**Find these details:**\n- People skating, sledding, playing golf on ice\n- Wealthy and poor mixing together\n- A couple in a private moment (left)\n- Children playing (center)\n- A man who has fallen (right foreground)\n\nAvercamp was deaf and mute, which may have sharpened his observational skills. Notice how he captures dozens of tiny narratives in one panoramic scene.\n\n---\n\n**Moving to Floor 0:** Dutch crafts and history",
