      "name": "Delftware Collection",
      "pid": "12",
      "text": "# Delftware Collection\n## Various Artists, 17th-18th Century\n\n![Delftware](assets/images/delftware.jpg)\n\n**Location:** Floor 0, Room 0.7  \n**QR Code:** RIJKS-DELFTWARE-009\n\n[audio](assets/audio/en/delftware.mp3)\n\n### Dutch Blue\n\nDelftware‚Äîthe iconic blue and white pottery‚Äîwas the Netherlands' answer to Chinese porcelain. When Dutch traders brought back porcelain from Asia via the VOC (Dutch East India Company), local potters in Delft began creating their own versions.\n\n**What made Delftware special:**\n- Tin-glazed earthenware (not true porcelain)\n- Hand-painted blue designs\n- Dutch scenes mixed with Asian motifs\n- Became wildly popular across Europe\n\n### Global Trade\n\nThis collection represents the Dutch Golden Age's global reach‚Äîtrade routes to Asia, artistic innovation at home, and the wealth that allowed Dutch families to fill their homes with beautiful objects.\n\n---\n\n**Tour almost complete!** A few more treasures await.",
